http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Kasaragod-school-arts-festival-to-get-under-way-on-Monday/article13976452.ece

The Revenue District School Arts Festival, a precursor to the 56th State Arts Festival, will get under way here from January 4. About 4,500 students from upper primary, high school and higher secondary sections will vie for honours in the five-day cultural event.Eight venues“The competitions, which will take place at eight venues named after rivers in the northern region, will be held at the Government Higher Secondary School, the Chinmaya Vidyalaya and Municipal Town Hall,” organising committee chairperson Beefathima Ibrahim told a press conference here on Friday.In the light of recent reports that the results of the events were being manipulated in other parts of the State, the authorities had decided to issue strict guidelines to the judging panel, Ms. Ibrahim, who is Kasaragod municipality chairperson, said.Elaborate arrangements have been made to accommodate as many as 5,000 viewers at the eight venues where the programmes are set to be held from 9.30 a.m. to 7.30 p.m.The services of National Cadet Corps, Student Police Cadets and Scouts & Guides have been solicited to assist the local police in ensuring the smooth conduct of programmes.The Kalotsavam will be inaugurated by N.A. Nellikkunnu, MLA, on Monday while the valedictory session on January 8 will be opened by P. Karunakaran, MP.